that will allow you do to as root:

```
$ grep gscrivano /etc/subuid
gscrivano:110000:65536

$ sudo podman run --rm --uidmap 0:1000:1  --subuidname gscrivano:1  alpine cat /proc/self/uid_map
         1     110000      65536
         0       1000          1
```

That will leave room for your custom `--uidmap`.

For more complex cases, it is always possible to use directly `--uidmap` and avoid completely `--subuidname`.
